<br>
From the TL 1.59 Report : <br>
<br>
<br>
Reflex Attack –<br>
<br>
The Following Test Results are a good read for the issues with reflex attack: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.drunkenfriar.com/forums/display_topic_threads.asp?ForumID=2&TopicID=1571&PagePosition=2">www.drunkenfriar.com/foru...Position=2</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
(From the December Report)<br>
<br>
Reflex Attack is the Friar unique realm ability. It is advertised as:<br>
<br>
“For 30 seconds, you will automatically counter-attack any melee attack immediately, with no timer. There is no limit to the number of aattackers you can potentially Reflex Attack – any player or monster who attacks you will receive an immediate counter-attack.” <br>
<br>
This is false advertising. The Reflex Attack ability will NOT counter-attack “any melee attack immediately.” Actually, there are quite a few problems with it:<br>
<br>
1.     1.       If an incoming attack is evaded, parried, or blocked, Reflex Attack will not counter-attack.<br>
2.     2.       If an incoming attack is from a position that the Friar cannot face (i.e. from the back or side), Reflex Attack will not counter-attack.<br>
3.     3.       If attacks come in too quickly and too frequently, Reflex Attack will only counter-attack selectively based upon the Friar’s staff SPD reading. In other words, if a Savage is tossing swings very quickly, the Friar with a 5.0SPD staff will counter-attack every successful shot from the Savage that occurs every 5.0 seconds. This is a mere speculation of what is happening… there may be something much deeper and messed up than just this. A log of this behavior is available at request.<br>
<br>
Frankly, for what was advertised versus what we actually get, the Friar unique realm ability isn’t worth the 14 points for a 30 second “Hey I hope it works” joy-ride that can only be used every 30 minutes. <br>
<br>
Suggestions: Either make reflex attack work against all attacks, not just successful hits, or reduce its cost <p>Zavien Daehskar<br>
Celtic Mentalist<br>
